titles.title: Providing for consideration of the Senate amendment to the bill (H.R. 920) to extend the emergency unemployment compensation program, and for other purposes.

action.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 103-26, by Mr. Moakley.
Rule provides for consideration of senate amendment to H.R. 920.

calendar.text: Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 15.

action.text: Mr. Moakley moved to consider the resolution.
On motion to consider the resolution Agreed to by voice vote.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by voice vote.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: 3/4/1993--Introduced. Provides for the consideration of the Senate amendment to H.R. 920 (emergency unemployment compensation program extension).
